      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MCCRACKEN (8) was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten 5.5 lengths into third (22.56) at Murray Bridge in a Maiden over 395m. The form out of last race has been strong. Deserves a win and gets his chance. SPRINGVALE MARGI (2) copped a check in the run and finished a well held 9 lengths fifth (20.68) last time in a Maiden at this track over 342m. Rates a key player and gets chance to atone. ADHANA DEREK (6) failed to threaten on debut finishing sixth (32.45) at Gawler over 531m. Expected to do much better this time. GULF STREAM (1) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.",
